data.title: Cuban Food
data.text: Enjoyed their signature Cuban meal that they are known for.  It was delicious.  Great food, good value.

data.title: Great food
data.text: I have a lot of meals here. I used to get their pork sandwich which is great. But recently I have started getting their red snapper which is to die for. Tried their salmon which was good but snapper is better. If you like Cuban food with an international flair I highly recommend Felix. It's right on the Circle in Orange and you can't beat the view.

data.title: Lots of Food!
data.text: Lots of spicy food which is very tasty.  You get your money's worth. Located in the circle of Orange. Value is so good you will want to return.  One of the best places to try Cuban food.

data.title: A Great Find...Food Like Abuela Used To Make!
data.text: If you're looking for a touch of Cuba, you can't go wrong here!  The recipes have to come from family elders...the food is just that good!  Welcoming atmosphere, incredibly priced.  Go once, and you'll be hooked!  If outdoor dining is available, try it!

data.title: Cuban Food in Orange
data.text: Very extensive menu, prices are reasonable.  Breakfasts are good and plentiful.  Dinners include soup or salad and dessert - great value.  Love the plantains that come with most entrees.  Good bread.  They are good about substitutions too.  Friendly and competent staff - good service.  Only downside is the smoke that billows over from the cigar shop - makes it feel like Cuba, I guess - but if you are sensitive to smoke, you will have to eat inside.

data.title: Breakfast on weekends
data.text: The food is overall good, but the breakfast on weekends is actually great. Take advantage of the weather and seat outside for an early morning breakfast. It is actually very good.

data.title: Sunday brunch, very nice patio for dining and people watching.
data.text: Food was very good and I had never had cuban food before. The black beans served are the best I have ever had. The service was quick but our server was not overly friendly. I had the ham and fruit cup and my husband had an egg dish with chorizo, black beans and corn tortillas. We were both very happy with what we ordered.

data.title: Chicken Cordon Bleu
data.text: Excellent food. I got the chicken cordon bleu. You get a lot of food. Very friendly staff. Comes with bread, salad, and desert.

data.title: Awesome
data.text: Not fancy.  Amazing food, great service, and free dessert-how rare is that these days.  They have great cuban food on an extensive menu.  Easy to get a table.

data.title: Outstanding Fun Cuban Fare
data.text: We have been coming to this restaurant for the last 20 years, or so, when we are visiting Orange County. The first time was on a whim, every other time has been with intent. The food and service are both first-rate. We have eaten both inside and on the patio/sidewalk and prefer the outside atmosphere even though it is next to a tobacco shop. Sort of gives it an authentic Cuban feel, anyway. I can't say what plate is my favorite as I have never been disappointed. One suggestion; when going, try to get there early in the meal service time. Later times will back up considerably with a long wait for seating. 3-5 p.m. seems to be good. Any later and you'll be on the waiting list, but it WiLL be worth it!

data.title: Excellent  Cuban food!!
data.text: This is so close to Chapman and is such a wonderful meal!  The prices are amazing with how much food they serve!  The sangria is very good as are the tostones.

data.title: Cuban Delight
data.text: Felix's is always superb.  The food is excellent and the service delightful.  Always one of my favorite places.

data.title: Authentic Cuban flavors!!
data.text:
On the Trendy Orange Circle, this small family cafe is a real find! My son and I were in town for business and he suggested we eat lunch at Felix. 
Not a fancy place, but the menu is filled with wonderful authentic dishes, and the portions are generous! If you love Cuban, this is the real deal!
I ordered the Roasted Pork and the sauce was amazing! served with earthy seasoned Black beans and rice and a generous side of sweet Plantains. Better flavor than I have had at places far fancier!! My son had a traditional Cubano sandwich and said it was the most authentic he has tasted!
The service was friendly and fast, but not obnoxious. We sat near the window and enjoyed people watching as we dined.
I need to bring my Husband back to  experience the food! It was that good!  So nice to see family businesses flourish and such good food!

data.title: We are so happy this place is in Orange!
data.text: We had a pork dish on their red sided menu and it was the best pork dish we've ever had. We definitely will be going back again and again. I really enjoyed their mojito, and the only bad thing is they only serve it inside. Last visit we were able to enjoy a wine sangria outside.

data.title: Cuban Favorite
data.text: Since writing our review last summer, we have been back six or seven times for lunch.  The last two times I had something other than my favorite Roasted Chicken Cubano with garlic, lemon, and herbs.  A couple of weeks ago, I tried their Carne Con Papas which is like a boneless beef stew with potatoes and green olives.  It was very tasty and I will definitely have it again.  Last week, I tried their Palomilla Grilled Steak which is pounded out very thin and topped with onions.  It was also very good.  Most of Café Felix's dishes include black beans, rice, and maduros (which I believe are cooked plantains).   My wife always has here favorite Pollo Criollo which is a skinless, grilled chicken breast with garlic and lemon.  Next time you are in Orange on the circle, you should try this place, especially if you haven't tried Cuban food before.

data.title: Busy Place
data.text:
For starters I've never eaten Cuban food and part of my 3 star rating may just be because I discovered I'm not a fan of Cuban food. The food did arrive promptly and was piping hot.

Another negative for me is that I'm not a big fan of being seated so close to others that you feel as if you're dining with them. They really pack you in here.

On the positive side the staff was friendly and attentive and the prices and portions were great.

data.title: Great Breakfast Menu
data.text: My wife's family lives a short walk from here. This was my second visit for breakfast. I love that the menu is so extensive and that they offer dishes that are familiar but just different enough. The prices are good and the portions substantial. I'm sure that my wife and I will return here multiple times in the future.

data.title: Felix Continental Café offers an amazing breakfast, brunch and dinner.
data.text: Felix Continental Café offers an amazing breakfast, brunch and dinner.  I've dined here twice for breakfast outdoors.  The staff is very attentive.  Last visit I had the salmon medallions, a piece of breakfast burrito and pancakes.  Everything was delicious.  Orange juice is fresh squeezed.  Dogs ordered a side of ham and are welcome on the patio.  I've also had dinner here with satisfying portions to go.  Recommend dining here for any time of day.  Great spot.

data.title: We are glad we revisited this gem in Orange.
data.text: We always forget about this place in Orange.  We had tasted their roasted pork on the Orange Trolley Wine Tour and decided to revisit them.  We are so glad we did!  My husband and I shared a few delicious appetizers, the roasted pork dinner, a few great mojitos, and dessert. It was a fabulous meal. We'll be going back soon!

data.title: Food out of a can
data.text: Don't go here if you want authentic cuban food.  Everything is made to be authentic however all the ingrediants are out of a can which makes everything taste very average
